## Guidelines

> Note: This is a modular JavaFX desktop application with MySQL integration. The upgrade focuses on modernizing the Java runtime and dependencies to take advantage of Java 25 features and improvements.

## Options

- Working branch: modernize/java-20260526223045 (already created by coordinator)
- Run tests before and after the upgrade: false (test folder is empty; no test code exists)

## Upgrade Goals

- **Java**: 21 → 25
- **Maintain JavaFX desktop application functionality** with Java 25 compatibility

## Technology Stack

| Technology/Dependency    | Current | Min Compatible | Why Incompatible                               |
| ------------------------ | ------- | -------------- | ---------------------------------------------- |
| Java                     | 21      | 25             | User requested                                 |
| Maven Compiler Plugin    | 3.x (default) | 3.11.0         | 3.11+ recommended for better Java 25 support |
| JavaFX (controls, fxml)  | 21      | 25             | Java 25 requires JavaFX 25.x for full compatibility |
| MySQL Connector J        | 9.0.0   | 9.0.0+         | Compatible with Java 25; no change needed     |

## Derived Upgrades

1. **JavaFX 21 → JavaFX 25.x**: Java 25 requires matching JavaFX version for module system and platform compatibility. Update all JavaFX artifacts (controls, fxml, graphics) to version 25.
2. **maven-compiler-plugin → 3.11.0+**: Explicit configuration recommended for Java 25 support; ensures javac compatibility.
3. **Maven: Ensure 3.9+**: Maven 3.9.x recommended (3.8.x is EOL but still functional). Installation/verification will happen in Step 1.

